27185.credit_line: Gift of Wallace Seligman and Robert King
27185.provenance: Wallace Seligman and Robert King; given to the John Herron Art Institute, now the Indianapolis Museum of Art, in 1954.

extended_text.content:
Some containers from the arctic region are woven from baleen, a hornlike material, which makes up a fringed food filter in the mouths of whales.

Although baskets originated as utilitarian containers, they have, since the 1800s become an important art form for sale to outsiders.

Basketry containers have been made by Native Americans for over 10,000 years.
